The paper deals with nonadaptive group testing, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and involves designing efficient algorithms for testing a large number of items (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the performance of practical algorithms and gives upper bounds, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and statistics (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the sparsity of the testing matrix, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
